extends layout

block head
  - var canonicalUrl = 'https://www.getsoberspokane.com/liberty-lake-recovery-resources.html'
  title Addiction Recovery & Therapy Sources in Liberty Lake, WA
  meta(name="description" content="Discreet, professional addiction recovery resources in Liberty Lake, WA. Find private therapy, intensive outpatient programs, and local support connections.")
  script(type="application/ld+json").
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "LocalBusiness",
      "name": "Get Sober Spokane",
      "url": "https://www.getsoberspokane.com",
      "logo": "https://www.getsoberspokane.com/assets/img/logo.png",
      "telephone": "(509) 389-9350",
      "email": "getsoberspokane@outlook.com",
      "areaServed": {
        "@type": "City",
        "name": "Liberty Lake",
        "addressRegion": "WA"
      }
    }

block content

  header.bg-primary.text-white.py-5(style="margin-top: 76px;")
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8.text-center
          h1.display-5.fw-bold Recovery Resources in Liberty Lake, WA
          p.lead.mt-3 Professional, discreet addiction support along the eastern corridor.

  section.page-section
    .container.px-4.px-lg-5
      .row.justify-content-center
        .col-lg-8
          p.lead.mt-4
            | Nestled between Spokane Valley and the Idaho border, Liberty Lake is a quiet, rapidly growing community. The challenges of addiction and mental health don't skip the suburbs. Many professionals and families in Liberty Lake seek high-quality, discreet resources to tackle substance use disorders before they completely derail their careers or home lives. 

          // Professional Outpatient Focus
          h2.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-clipboard-check.text-primary.me-2
            | Private Practice &amp; Outpatient Rehab
          p For many employed professionals, leaving for 30 days is impossible. Connecting with local Intensive Outpatient Programs (IOPs) or private therapists along the I-90 corridor is often the safest route.
          ul
            li 
              strong Local Private Therapists: 
              | Liberty Lake and the adjacent Spokane Valley host dozens of private, licensed mental health counselors specializing in addiction, trauma (EMDR), and cognitive behavioral therapy.
            li 
              strong Intensive Outpatient (IOP): 
              | Treatment centers located just 10 minutes away in the Valley offer flexible evening programs designed to accommodate standard work schedules.
            li 
              strong Corporate EAP Utilization: 
              | Many Liberty Lake tech and business employers offer robust Employee Assistance Programs (EAPs) that fully cover the cost of outpatient counseling and initial substance abuse assessments with complete anonymity.
          a.btn.btn-outline-primary(href="/medical-mental-health.html" onclick="gtag('event', 'resources_click', {event_category: 'engagement', event_label: 'therapy_liberty_lake'})")
            i.bi.bi-arrow-right.me-2
            | Find Therapy &amp; Mental Health Help

          // Community Connections
          h2.mt-5
            i.bi.bi-people-fill.text-primary.me-2
            | Finding a Sober Community
          p Isolating in the suburbs is a fast track to a relapse. Getting plugged into the fellowship is essential.
          ul
            li 
              strong Specialized 12-Step Meetings: 
              | The Valley corridor hosts specific meetings for almost every demographic, including men's stags, women's meetings, and professionals-only AA groups, offering an added layer of privacy.
            li 
              strong The Parks &amp; Outdoors: 
              | The Liberty Lake Regional Park and Centennial Trail are prime grounds for the Spokane sober community's outdoor meetups and hiking groups. Stay active, naturally.
            li 
              strong Our Online Forum: 
              | Want to ask questions about local resources anonymously before walking into a clinic? Jump on our local forum.
          a.btn.btn-outline-primary(href="/community-forum.html" onclick="gtag('event', 'resources_click', {event_category: 'engagement', event_label: 'forum_liberty_lake'})")
            i.bi.bi-arrow-right.me-2
            | Connect Anonymously

          // Immediate Help
          .mt-5.p-4.bg-light.rounded-3
            h2.h4
              i.bi.bi-telephone-fill.text-danger.me-2
              | Connect with Help Now
            p Don't wait until the weekend is over. Help is available 24/7.
            ul.mb-3
              li
                strong Suicide &amp; Crisis Lifeline:
                |  988 (Call or Text)
              li
                strong WA Recovery Help Line:
                |  1-866-789-1511 (Opioid, gambling, and mental health referrals)
            a.btn.btn-primary.me-2(href="/resource-directory.html" onclick="gtag('event', 'resources_click', {event_category: 'engagement', event_label: 'all_resources_liberty_lake'})")
              i.bi.bi-list-ul.me-2
              | Access Full Directory
            a.btn.btn-danger(href="tel:18667891511" onclick="gtag('event', 'phone_click', {event_category: 'contact', event_label: 'helpline_liberty_lake'})")
              i.bi.bi-telephone.me-2
              | Call WA Help Line
